726108f-a.title: Queens: Atlantic Avenue - 109th Street
726108f-a.text:
Atlantic Avenue, at 109th Street, viewing across the Long sland Railroad tracks and showing a pedestrian walk
across the tracks.
P. L. Sperr  May 7, 1934

726109f-a.title: Queens: Atlantic Avenue - 109th Street
726109f-a.text:
(1) Atlantic Avenue, east from 109th Street, showing the Long Ialand Railroad tracks fenced off by a wooden fence and dividing the avenue into two separate lanes. At 110th treet is the
Clarenceville railroad station.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: May 7, 1934
(2) The railroad station at 11Oth Street, seen from the north lane of the avenue. On the right is the building of the Morris
Park Council of the Knights of Columbus.
P. L. Sperr  View 2: May 7, 1934
